{[showcards W:DA N:D3]

You are East. The bidding has been as shown. Partner led the \CA. Seeing your \C3 he next played the \DA. What will you play on this trick?

Play the \D2.

Normally with this holding you would play the \D9 to encourage West to play a second \D through dummy's \D Q 10.

But this time you really want him to take his \CK. So play the discouraging \D2 and hope he gets the message to go back to \Cs. If he does play the \CK next it will win and he can then give you a \C ruff.}
[Play "W"]CA

